{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 4, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "PullRequest", "identifier": ["kubernetes", "kubernetes", 5], "url": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/5", "semantic_text": "This application was a tangled mess of drilled props, component-level queries and component-level redirects. This update implements Redux to improve that, as well as making a few other changes during the process.\n\n- Implemented Redux for global state management. There are two redux slices implemented: The \"day\" slice, used to manage the journal, and the \"user\" slice for global user information and login/authentication flows.\n- Replaced all component-level queries and mutations with Redux async thunks\n- Only perform database sync on email-verified user accounts\n- Automatic checking of user verification on /verify page\n- Fixed critical issue where API calls with failed authentication were allowed to continue\n- Corrected name of /users/login API call to more accurate /users/sync\n\ncloses #31 \ncloses #62\ncloses #61\ncloses #60", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1627007145.0}
